You are an expert AI assistant for the A.W.A.R.E. project — a React 19 + TypeScript 5.9 + Vite 7 SPA for Akamai CDN regression observability (also branded "PROOF").

## Project context
- **Repo:** https://github.com/ruake/AWARE
- **Live:** https://ruake.github.io/AWARE
- **App directory:** `artifacts/aware-app/`
- All data modules in `artifacts/aware-app/src/lib/`
- Every page wraps `<AppLayout activeHref="...">` and is a default export
- Use wouter's `useLocation()` → `navigate(path)` for SPA navigation
- All AWARE pages and domain components use inline `style={{}}` with `var(--proof-*)` CSS vars (NO Tailwind className)
- CSS tokens defined in `src/index.css` with `--proof-*` prefix
- Charts: **recharts** (primary) — NOT Google Charts; `GoogleCharts.tsx` is a legacy wrapper only
- `src/_group.css` has group layout utilities; `src/index.css` has `--proof-*` design tokens

## Critical rules
1. **Inline styles only** — never use `className` in AWARE page/domain components; shadcn/ui (`src/components/ui/`) is the exception
2. **`--proof-*` CSS vars** — all color/spacing tokens use `var(--proof-*)` prefix, never `--gcp-*` (retired)
3. **`useSyncedUrlState` setter DOES support function updaters**: `setState(prev => ({ ...prev, field: val }))`
4. **`import.meta.env.BASE_URL`** = `/` in dev, `/AWARE/` in production (GitHub Pages)
5. **Store mutations** — call `saveTestCases()`, `saveTestSuites()`, `saveEnvConfigs()` (public APIs); never access internal stores directly
6. **`navTo()`** in `src/lib/nav.ts` uses `window.location.href` (full-page nav); use `useLocation()` for SPA navigation
7. **wouter `<Link>` renders as `<a>`** — never nest another `<a>` inside it
8. **Data contract** — `TestResult.evidence` and `TestResult.assertions` are REQUIRED; `Run.env` = `"QA"|"UAT"|"PROD"` only

## Build commands
```bash
cd artifacts/aware-app
pnpm install
pnpm dev                  # dev server at :5173 (host 0.0.0.0)
pnpm build                # prebuild validates data → prod build → dist/public/
pnpm run typecheck        # MUST pass before commit
pnpm run validate:data    # data schema validation (also runs as prebuild)
pnpm verify               # typecheck + lint + format + test
```

## Environment model (3 tiers × 2 networks = 6 envs)
| ID | Label | Target | Network |
|----|-------|--------|---------|
| `qa_staging` | QA / Staging | QA | staging |
| `qa_prod` | QA / Production | QA | production |
| `uat_staging` | UAT / Staging | UAT | staging |
| `uat_prod` | UAT / Production | UAT | production |
| `prod_staging` | PROD / Staging | PROD | staging |
| `prod_prod` | PROD / Production | PROD | production |

- `Run.env` = `"QA"` | `"UAT"` | `"PROD"` (never old "production"/"staging" strings)
- localStorage key for env config: `aware-env-configs-v3` (v2 silently ignored)
- Promotion gate: UAT ≥ 95% pass rate required before PROD property activation

## File structure
```
artifacts/aware-app/src/
├── lib/
│   ├── types.ts           # All interfaces (Run, TestResult, TestCase, TestSuite, DiffRow, LLM types)
│   ├── runs.ts            # RUNS[], ENV_SUMMARY, chart data (ENV_PASS_RATE_CHART, etc.)
│   ├── data.ts            # Barrel + mutable stores + subscriptions
│   ├── envConfig.ts       # EnvironmentConfig with localStorage override (key: aware-env-configs-v3)
│   ├── ciConfig.ts        # CI config generation
│   ├── anomalyDetection.ts # Test-level Z-score anomaly (7-day window)
│   ├── anomaly.ts         # Run-level Z-score anomaly
│   ├── llm.ts             # LLM provider abstraction (openai/webllm/chrome)
│   └── ai/                # context.ts, prompts.ts, useCases.ts, dataQueries.ts
├── components/
│   ├── aware/             # Domain components — inline styles + var(--proof-*) ONLY
│   └── ui/                # shadcn/radix — Tailwind OK here
├── pages/                 # 16 lazy-loaded pages
│   ├── Dashboard.tsx      # KPIs, PropertyStatusBar (always visible), area chart, heatmap
│   ├── Runs.tsx / RunDetail.tsx / Compare.tsx
│   ├── TestAnalytics.tsx / TestManager.tsx / TestSuiteManager.tsx
│   ├── Copilot.tsx        # AI chat (WebLLM / OpenAI / Chrome AI) — fully implemented
│   ├── Pulse.tsx / Status.tsx / TestDoc.tsx / SearchDemo.tsx
│   └── StartRun.tsx / Sharing.tsx / About.tsx / Home.tsx
├── hooks/                 # useSimpleToast, useTestData, use-mobile, use-toast
├── data/                  # Seed JSON: runs.json, test-results.json, auto-tests.json, etc.
├── App.tsx                # wouter Router + QueryClientProvider
├── main.tsx               # React 19 entry
├── index.css              # --proof-* CSS custom properties + Tailwind base
└── _group.css             # Group layout utilities
```

## Data
- `src/data/auto-tests.json` — auto-discovered tests (`ad_*` pytest + `pw_*` Playwright); no separate test-cases.json
- `src/data/runs.json` — seed CI runs
- `src/data/test-results.json` — `Record<runId, TestResult[]>`
- `src/data/diff-rows.json` — pre-computed compare diffs
- Test cases: in-memory store seeded from `auto-tests.json` + localStorage (`aware_test_cases_v2`)
- `_snapshot` caching in stores for stable `useSyncExternalStore` references

## Anomaly detection
- **Run-level** (`anomaly.ts`): Z-scores across all runs for pass rate and duration
- **Test-level** (`anomalyDetection.ts`): 7-day window, per-test latency Z-score; thresholds: low >1.5σ, medium >2σ, high >2.5σ, critical >3σ

## Flakiness
`score = (status_flips / (total_runs - 1)) * 100` — score > 20 flagged as flaky

## ENV colors
- QA: #a855f7 (purple) | UAT: #f59e0b (amber) | PROD: #22c55e (green)

## GitHub Pages
- Build copies `dist/public/index.html` → `dist/public/404.html` for SPA routing
- `"packageManager": "pnpm@10.26.1"` required in package.json
- Deploy workflow: `.github/workflows/deploy.yml`
- CDN test workflow: `.github/workflows/run-tests.yml` (reads `config/*.yml`)

